library(tidyverse)
library(readxl)
library(gganimate)
library(lme4)
url1 <- "https://query.data.world/s/tw3oaknxjlqods27xzzbpa3do4rmfr"
p1f <- tempfile()
download.file(url1, p1f, mode="wb")
online_data_chapter_2_whr_2017_actual <- read_excel(path = p1f)
#Rename dataset
dataset <- online_data_chapter_2_whr_2017_actual

#rename variables 
dataset <- mutate(dataset, happiness=`Life Ladder`)

dataset <- mutate(dataset, GDP=`Log GDP per capita`)

dataset <- mutate(dataset, life_Expecantcy=`Healthy life expectancy at birth`)

dataset <- mutate(dataset, Freedom=`Freedom to make life choices`)

dataset <- mutate(dataset, corruption= `Perceptions of corruption`)

dataset <- mutate(dataset, Government_Confidence= `Confidence in national government`)        

target <- c("Austria", "Belgium", "Bulgaria", "Croatia", "Cyprus", "Czech Republic", "Denmark", "Estonia", "Finland", "France", "Germany", "Greece", "Hungary", "Ireland", "Italy", "Latvia", "Lithuania", "Luxembourg", "Malta", "Netherlands", "Poland", "Portugal", "Romania", "Slovakia", "Slovenia", "Spain", "Sweden", "United Kingdom")
Europe_data <- filter(dataset, country %in% target)

Europe_data <- Europe_data %>% filter(!is.na(GDP))
dataset3 <- Europe_data %>% group_by(year) %>% summarise(mean_happiness= mean(happiness),mean_GDP=mean(GDP))
ggplot(dataset3, aes(x=year, y=mean_happiness, group = year, colour = year)) + geom_point()    

ggplot(dataset3, aes(x=year, y=mean_GDP, group = year, colour =year)) + geom_point()

ggplot(dataset3, aes(x=mean_happiness, y=mean_GDP)) + geom_smooth() +geom_point()
## `geom_smooth()` using method = 'loess' and formula 'y ~ x'

ggplot(Europe_data, aes(x=happiness, y= GDP)) + geom_smooth(method = "lm") +geom_point()      

model1 <- lmer(happiness ~ GDP * Freedom + (1 | country), data=Europe_data, REML= TRUE)
qqnorm(residuals(model1))
qqline(residuals(model1))                  

modelnull <- lmer(happiness ~ (1 | country), data=Europe_data, REML = TRUE)

anova(model1, modelnull)
## refitting model(s) with ML (instead of REML)
